##Check, persuade back, loudspeakers, road closure, such as rural pneumonia prevention

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

ORAL ACCOUNT OF THE WAR Epidemic, a special column launched by COVID-19 during the outbreak of pneumonia, records the observations and feelings of those who experienced the epidemic. This article is the 2nd issue, the 1st Issue Please See"I fight pneumonia in Wuhan".

By Yan Lijiao Tang Yahua and Meng Yana

Yu Fan, dawn, Ming Ming Ming, Su Qi

Editor | Zhou Changfan

With a large number of people returning home during the Spring Festival, limited medical and health conditions, and weak awareness of prevention and control, many rural areas have become dead ends of prevention and control. At a meeting of the COVID-19 on Jan. 26, it was clearly stated that great importance should be attached to the prevention and control of the epidemic in rural areas.

The epidemic of new crown pneumonia has continued to spread. Since the outbreak of the epidemic, despite the cancellation of temple fairs, rallies and other Spring Festival activities in many places, village committees have been actively promoting the "no visiting relatives or friends during the Spring Festival" policy, and some towns have even closed roads, but there are still rural elders do not pay enough attention, do not wear masks, do not listen to advice, normal visits to friends and relatives, big banquet.

Some villagers believe that they are far from Wuhan, and the village population mobility is not strong, in the geographical sense of security. Others felt that they had nothing to do with the outbreak because the village's confirmed cases had not been made public. But more and more villages and towns are paying attention. In Zhoukou, Henan Province, village secretaries work from 4 a.m. to 12 p.m. to keep an eye on the epidemic. In Xinyang, Henan Province, excavators have been brought in, barriers have been erected at village intersections, and road closures are being implemented in other areas. In Jingmen and Jingzhou, the consciousness of the villagers, who do not take it seriously at all, is changing.

During the Spring Festival, ran CAIJING interviewed villagers in seven towns and villages in Hubei, Henan and Hebei, hoping to learn more about the real situation of rural epidemic prevention through them.

I don't know if I can go home now

All sides are counting me

Prince Heng, 20, a villager in Chongju, Hebei Province

I'm a Wuhan University of Technology Junior. Last December, I was still in Wuhan, the epidemic has a warning, but did not take seriously, our dormitory as before out to eat, play. On January 12, I arrived in Dingzhou from Hankou, and my family drove me back to the county seat. It wasn't until a few days after I got home, around January 20, that the news of the new type of pneumonia in Wuhan became so overwhelming that I passively received it and began to pay attention.

I recall carefully, from leaving Wuhan to now half a month, I did not appear any fever, chest tightness, headache, sneezing, and every night without breakfast, go out wearing thin, still not sick.

These days really see the power of the country, I am usually no one will pay attention to the small role, just because studying in Wuhan.

Thirty (24) , the first day (25) these two days I returned to the rural home, as usual. Calling me and everyone around me. New Year's Eve in the morning, the former class teacher and students of High School Liberal Arts and Sciences Division called to greet me, the residential committee asked my mother my situation. On the first day of the Lunar New Year, the residential committee, the residential property so that my mother must control I do not let out, the residential area where the Chengxi Village Committee called my grandfather let control me. The third day (27) morning again by the high school where the City Education Bureau more than 7:00 Phone inquiries about the situation.

My father is also being asked to count me because he is a member of the village committee in my hometown. Because of the epidemic, my father began to work overtime on the afternoon of the 1st day of the 1st day of the Lunar New Year. The county and the village had meetings. On the morning of the 2nd day of the Lunar New Year, he made a patrol list on his computer, dividing the village's young men into 20 small teams to patrol.

On my way back from my hometown to the county seat, I pass several villages, some of which have been sealed off with big stones moved by excavators. I don't know if I can go back to the county from my hometown. I'm afraid if I don't go back, I won't. My home area in the county seat has been cordoned off, not allowed to enter the car, I have now passed Virus latency, but I do not know whether to enter the community. If I could get home, I wouldn't go out. I'm being counted.

The network news is too much too chaotic, I now only believe the National Formal Authority Department of the news, and I have contact in Wuhan friends. Other than that, I don't believe any of the personal messages retweeted by my family on Weibo, Weibo, Douyin, Kuaishou. The narrow channels through which individuals receive information, coupled with the fact that most of them are not highly educated and have no experience in dealing with such a national event, make any individual statement too unreliable.

During this period, I also received a lot of students, friends of the care, thank you very much, I am surrounded by people do not have any different attitude towards me, because I am very healthy, these days to see friends, family also do not have that kind of harsh mouth. I personally promise that in the next few days, I myself will not leave the house unless absolutely necessary, to protect others and to protect myself.

Working from 4:00 a.m. to 12:00 P.M

It's the best I can do right now

Mr Liu, 50, secretary of a village in Zhoukou, Henan Province

I am the village secretary of our village, took office in the second half of 2002, just in time for SARS. At the time of SARS, all returnees were sent to a school in the village for quarantine, which lasted for seven days. I think it's a lot like SARS.

This year I received the notice from the town on January 21, when all the village secretaries went to the town at 6 o'clock in the afternoon to hold the "epidemic prevention and Control Conference. ". The meeting informed us that, according to the notice of the pneumonia headquarters office of the COVID-19 and the actual situation of the epidemic, all villages should strictly control the checkpoints, so as to have a command tent, on duty, have records, and stick to it 24 hours a day, eAT, rotate shifts. No very special circumstances, personnel, vehicles are not allowed to go out, let us strictly comply with the implementation. If there are any Wuhan returnees or those who have come into contact with Wuhan residents, they should be isolated at home for 14 days, set up a counter, take temperature every day, and have a contractor and responsible person in charge. If there is a fever during the period, immediately report to the Superior Epidemic Prevention and Control Center.

After returning to the village, the village doctors and village cadres in our village, a total of nine people began to sweep through the night. People returning home, no matter from where, as long as they return within the last 20 days, they should isolate themselves at home with their families. Because even if they don't come back from Wuhan, they risk coming into contact with the Wuhan people.

In the process, we will go door to door to persuade people not to be afraid, this virus is now defensible, most people can understand our work, plus TV, the Internet has been reminding people not to go out, to wear masks, if anyone comes out on his own, our cadres will follow him to supervise. Village doctors take temperature readings and check in every day. Common Fevers and colds need to be reported.

Village radio began at 5am with notes such as not visiting relatives, going out wearing masks, washing hands and so on, and continued until the end of the afternoon. We will drive the car door-to-door publicity, will also put up posters in the village, multi-publicity and mobilization.

Poster poster on Village Wall Source / interviewee

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Source / Interviewee of the village outbreak van

Slogan sources / Interviewees posted in the village

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Starting from January 26, every day at 5:30 pm, we also need to hold a teleconference with the county Party secretary and other county cadres on time to listen to the latest developments and work guidance, for example, they will tell us to do a good job of publicity, do not cause panic, do their own protective measures. Now the masses are gradually aware of the seriousness of the problem, they will not go out more, do not go to relatives, go out to wear a mask has become everyone's common sense. At present, the village has not yet found the return from Wuhan, the majority of the masses more obedient arrangement, the overall situation is still stable.

These days, the nine of US get up at 4:00 am every day, hold meetings, arrange work, then start to spread the news in the village, Canvass, wait until after 12:00 am to make sure the village road is empty, then go home to rest, there is no limit to the working hours, try to get the quarantine down to a solid level. My family will worry about me, too, but I'll take precautions, as far as my strength will take me.

Although some outside people now say that we are too indifferent to the returnees from Wuhan, and some people are afraid to say that they have returned from Wuhan, in fact this is also for the sake of their personal and family health, all we can do now is show them that they don't have to be afraid and that we can get through this together.

Road closure by excavators

I returned the ticket, and I stayed home

Chen Kai, 28, a villager in Xinyang, Henan Province

Although the epidemic situation is serious, the people of our village overall feel or understand, very calm. Some people have business at home or want to travel, a little bit urgent. The attention of the villagers is also very high, I did not have much to persuade the parents, but to disseminate some reliable information to them.

Not far from the village there will be loudspeakers, every day in the broadcast of the epidemic news, protection advice, and so on, the entire prevention and control atmosphere has been very strong. Parents, not only will watch TV news, but also often in the mobile phone brush Douyin, Kuaishou, wechat and so on, related information also contact a lot. In addition, village cadres have been mass messaging and text messaging.

The road into the village is closed. At about 10 a.m. on January 26, a rumbling sound came from outside the window. I looked out of the window and saw a working excavator and a trailer parked nearby, digging on the side of the road to "fill the road. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sources / Interviewees of road closure

The roadblock is at a t-junction about ten meters from our house, leading to three villages, which is also the junction of two towns. The first shovel of earth had just been heaped up, and a white car from the south drove up, but it had to stop at the mound.

There was still a crack in the road, between the excavator and the mound, but it did not have the courage to "squeeze" over, hesitated for about two minutes, turned away. Then more cars came, stopping, hesitating, turning around. In front of my home and my neighbor's house, it became a parking lot for a while. Vehicles from the north and the south turned back one after another.

I do not know whether it is because of the epidemic in my hometown or my father's awareness itself is high, he has been more alert and nervous than I have, had advance notice in the next city do not come back. After the village road closure my father called my elder sister in the county seat and urged them to hurry home.

Big sister husband and wife in the county mall operating a restaurant, January 25 evening received notice, the original Second Business Mall, has been temporarily delayed to the fifth opening. To this end, they drove overnight to the county, put some fresh food into the refrigerator, try to stop loss.

Then my father made several more phone calls, telling more friends and relatives to abandon their travel plans and stay home.

When the road was closed, my neighbor aunt was standing in front of my house. Her house was diagonally opposite my house. She said, "I have to turn over the earth this time. ". This intersection, there are people around, this "small Soil Hill" , just by five families surrounded. If you want to visit, you have to "cross the mountain" first. But for me, who never visits, it doesn't matter.

She talked to me for a few minutes, and she seemed a little lost. She and her husband live alone in a house on the edge of the village. If you want to enter the village, you must first "over the mountains" .

I also expressed a little worry: The village elderly, if the elderly who suddenly fell ill, his car can not get out, the ambulance can not get in. It might be better to have someone on guard and let them through selectively. Of course, standing guard is not necessarily in the outdoor, like this intersection, put some obstacles, send a staff in the neighborhood or my home can be "guard. ".

Back in my room, I clicked on 12306 and returned the ticket I had fought so hard for. My Dad says we can feed our family for a month.

Village officials go door to door to inform

GRANDPA's 70th birthday is canceled

Fan Fan, a 27-year-old villager in Jingmen, Hubei Province

My hometown is a small village below Jingmen, Hubei Province. I returned to Wuhan on January 9, when the company held an event here. After the January 17th event, I went back to my hometown. The epidemic had not yet broken out, but it had been deliberately and simply prevented when returning home, and most of the people on the street wearing masks were young.

Wuhan outbreak of the initial outbreak should be in 19 and 20, these two days have seen the news release of the epidemic situation. But the countryside guard consciousness is particularly weak, when I come back, the hometown basically nobody cares about this matter. At first, I tried to persuade my family to take precautions and put on a mask. But they wouldn't listen to anything I said, or even think I was trying to scare them. In the end, it was the village cadres who spoke. On the eve of the Lunar New Year, village cadres wearing masks went door-to-door to inform that there should be no group activities during the Spring Festival. People back home realized the seriousness and began to wear masks.

Catch up with Wuhan Fengcheng, this year in Jiangsu uncle and 111 people did not rush back, although the family is not together, but the reunion dinner still has to be prepared. GRANDPA's 70th birthday was cancelled due to the outbreak.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Village sources / interviewees

According to village custom, New Year's Day will go door-to-door to say hello, this year all cancelled, no relatives to pay New Year. They can't come either. The village is sealed off from village to village. Some village officials kept an eye on the roads leading into the village. At the entrance, stones and mud were piled up to keep people and cars out.

To tell the truth, after the outbreak of the city of Wuhan, I still have a psychological gap. Before I went back home, I had my hair done specially, and I was going to come back and meet my family and friends. Then I came back from Wuhan and isolated myself. This week, I also wear a mask at home, eating dishes and chopsticks have to be separated from the family, no one to talk, Weibo a hundred times a day brush. Today is the first time to go out, the village basically do not see people, on the road to see a mask, usually people on the road, now only a few magpies. The village hospital was open, but no one was there.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There's hardly anyone left in the village, sources / interviewees

Received the notice of the company, our Wuhan Branch Office after the Work Extension, is at Home Office status. Several of my classmates have quarantined themselves after working in Wuhan. Most of the friends in Wuhan work, but also in the north of Guangzhou, are very helpless, can only at home and so on company notice. A friend who had just lost his job years ago was looking for a job. He was so anxious to pay back his credit card.

These days, there is so much information on the Internet that there is really no way to judge whether it is true or false. However, donations from people from all walks of life and spontaneous support of the people in Wuhan City, the overall epidemic has been eased. And almost every province has a confirmed case. It's everybody's business.

I think the most useful thing we can do for society at present is to stay at home for 15 days before going out, keep an eye on the epidemic situation, take effective preventive measures, drink plenty of hot water and wash our hands frequently. The protection measures in the countryside are still too weak. We hope that more people will join the team to guard against the epidemic and hold the village together with the village leaders. Some towns in Henan have done a good demonstration, I think can be used for reference, visit training is very important.

A small place is a society of acquaintances who know the local conditions

But a poor sense of information

Marsching, 29, a villager in Cangzhou, Hebei Province

My home is in a small town in Cangzhou, Hebei Province, part of a rural-to-township transition. I came home on the 22nd, and there weren't that many people on the road wearing masks.

I have been concerned about the Wuhan epidemic, so the information is timely, I told my family that this is SARS, the family did not care at first. I told one of my brothers to stock up on face masks they couldn't get in Beijing, but he didn't listen, joking, "maybe I'll go to Beijing and sell them. "

Least of all, my father. On New Year's Eve, my father insisted on going out to visit an elderly relative, and I tried to talk him out of it. His reason is: the etiquette between rural relatives is much, some elders have to move around often, otherwise the relationship is weak. And he doesn't wear a mask, so it's not like he's going to visit people in a mask.

The city of Wuhan was closed on the 23rd, and news of the outbreak did not officially break for another two days. Then, hearing of a case in the province, the atmosphere in the town became tense. One after another relatives called to say that the Spring Festival does not move, Call New Year can be, we all began to be alert, this time the father gave up the idea of going out.

People in villages, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns, towns. The most exaggerated is, after the provincial cases, someone in the village said, the central to send a plane to spray disinfectant in the air.

On the second day of the eighth Lunar New Year, I heard that the town had finished its meeting, and then the loudspeakers in the square outside began to ring. All the morning, they were calling on everyone not to go out, not to visit relatives, not to go to places where people gathered. Next thing I knew, the town's hotels, restaurants, card rooms, bathhouses were all closed, and the village paths were all sealed.

Small places are a society of acquaintances, and the local people are quite familiar with the local situation. When the blockade began, it became a common task for all to monitor people returning from the field. If someone comes from out of town, the news will be sent to the local area immediately, and people will be more alert. But in general, our local prevention and control of the epidemic measures are very orderly and civilized.

Officials should release the specific villages and towns where cases have been confirmed

Avoid pollyannaism

30-year-old villager from Jingzhou, Chongming Province

Jingzhou is about two or three hours'drive from Wuhan, and there is a lot of migration between Jingzhou and Wuhan. At present, publicity has a certain effect, but the attention of villagers is not too high, fortunately, awareness of prevention is constantly improving.

At the village level, there are currently three measures: Registration of all returnees is completed before New Year's Eve; announcements are broadcast on a daily loop so that people do not drop by, and all dining activities such as the red, white and wedding events are banned, including some notices; The roads out of the town are basically closed. Our village next to a road out of town, the equivalent of the village road has been closed. We also have the custom of going back to our mother's house during the Spring Festival. Now the road to our mother's house is blocked.

The road out of the village is closed

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the village the outside information which the ordinary contact is not many, my home side has a loudspeaker. After the outbreak, the village increased the frequency of the broadcast. On the whole, the publicity has had some effect. We actually have a lot of friends and relatives back from Wuhan. Rural people like to idle each other, chatter, this year's Spring Festival, we basically have no offline contacts, are online wechat New Year. I grew up next door to my house, and I never tried to talk to him. Even the ones who came back from the city. They just had dinner, stayed a day or two, and left.

If it's someone from Wuhan, everyone will be very sensitive. People returning from the city also feared they would bring the disease into the village, as dozens of cases had been confirmed in Jingzhou.

But my general feeling is that most people in the village still don't pay enough attention. Our village is relatively empty, unlike the city so dense, relatively scattered households, personnel mobility is not large, a certain sense of geographical security. There is anxiety, and more people's anxiety is playful and self deprecating, and they feel far away from them, even though they are in Hubei. Because even though the official figures for the total number of confirmed cases are out, we don't really know where they are. Sometimes there are rumors, there's no way to know for sure. I suggest we make it clear which town and village we're dealing with.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Some villagers began to wear masks source / interviewee

And, of course, people's defenses are changing. When I first came back, there was no one in the village wearing a mask, and there was no other protection, except that I took it very seriously. With the closure of Wuhan and the town road closure, the villagers consciousness took a very big turn. On December twenty-nine, I went to the nearest market to buy masks, which were no longer available. After the New Year, supermarkets and markets even food is not available, many businesses are not out of the stall. I actually saw a couple of people wearing masks today, for the first time in years.

Village officials have sent out epidemic prevention messages on various wechat groups

The parents listened at once

Zhang Jian, 30, a villager in Hengshui, Hebei Province

My home is in the south of Hebei Province, about 300 kilometers from Beijing. This year, because of the epidemic, I chose to hitch a ride home, a three-hour train ride that took me all day.

Back home, the village has been used to pile up a thick "barrier" , there are guards, blocking and registration of strange vehicles, not local cars are not allowed to enter, equivalent to the half-closed village.

Sources / interviewees of outbreak checkpoints set up in villages

After two days at home, the village clinic began going door-to-door to register the migrants'personal information. The village hung a red banner -- no gatherings, no public places, no public transportation. Village loudspeakers broadcast daily calls to reduce New Year's, family meals and other activities, broadcast several times a day.

Compared with the Spring Festival in peacetime, in accordance with the requirements of epidemic prevention, my family has no other activities except going to graves and burning paper, no more relatives, no family dinner, the New Year is a lot of desolation, really "no taste. ".

My family generally attaches importance to the prevention of the epidemic, I also prepared for my parents mask and hand sanitizer, but other people in the village, mask wearing rate is not high.

I also shared the news of the outbreak in my family group, and the extent of it. In persuading the parents did not have a lot of effort, but the father at first is not used to, said several times did not wear a mask, until the second day of the second day of going out to the grave, I put it on him hard, midway supervised several times not to let him pick.

At first my parents didn't hear about the pneumonia in Wuhan, then I learned about it through TV and short cell phone videos, then I forced them to wear masks, wash their hands and teach them how to protect themselves. One of the turning point in time, is the village cadres in each group of Wechat sent voice, to strengthen the epidemic of science, they all of a sudden listen.

Later, they were also closely monitoring the outbreak, with the father watching short videos on a Toutiao client, and the mother watching through radio, television and wechat groups, which spread quickly through villages and towns, even which shop mask black heart price do not go, who have Wuhan back population is clear.

During the SARS period, I was still in primary school, wearing a mask every day, temperature, the head teacher every day in the classroom boil vinegar. Compared to the previous, the spread of information about the epidemic, the proportion of short video should not be low, with television and other traditional media to compete with the trend.

The Mask I had left at home, bought from an e-commerce store. This Spring Festival afraid not enough, and respectively in Taobao and Pinduoduo bought some. Pinduoduo bought a pack of disposable medical masks, feeling no increase in price but also no delivery. Taobao bought two bags, are a bag of medical masks, not shipped; a bag of anti-toxic haze mask, 20 only 208 yuan, sent EMS, the speed is very slow.

On January 26th, at 3-4 o'clock, an anti-toxin plane flew by, and village officials were notified on wechat groups. That day I hesitated to go back to Beijing. Guoxin Development before the conference, a small number of friends have bought tickets to return to Beijing, the third day of the return trip more. After the press conference, I promised that Beijing would not close the city, schools and other educational institutions delayed the start of school, many friends, including myself, are no longer in a hurry to return to Beijing.
